<subSubSection pageId="81" pageNumber="358" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="81.[172,1380,1750,3044]" pageId="81" pageNumber="358">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[173,910,2774,2807]" pageId="81" pageNumber="358">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
Probably similar to the Whitethroated Woodrat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="81" pageNumber="358" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="81.[172,1380,1750,3044]" pageId="81" pageNumber="358">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[174,522,2857,2886]" pageId="81" pageNumber="358">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The IUCN Red List. Little is known about the Black-tailed Woodrat, but given its somewhat restricted distribution, it is in need of a conservation assessment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
